Added a new security feature for payment confirmation. 

We have added two-step verification to confirm all payments made from a Holvi account. In the Holvi App, users must now verify all payments with a security passcode delivered by SMS, as well as with a users Holvi password. The password for payment verification is the same used to sign in the Holvi account.

The change is due to new requirements that the Second Payment Service Directive has on Strong Customer Authentication (SCA).To comply with the new legislation, we must ask customers to authenticate themselves with two different elements, an SMS passcode and their Holvi password, when making payments.

The new security step can be found on the payment verification page. Previously, a user was asked to verify payments a the passcode sent via SMS, but now in addition to the passcode, user is also asked to verify the payment with their Holvi password.
